# Intermediate CA for cac.es (T148 hardening).
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS:
#   cac.es serves an INCOMPLETE TLS certificate chain — the server sends ONLY its
#   leaf (`*.cac.es`) and omits this intermediate. Browsers and `curl` tolerate that
#   (they fetch the missing intermediate via the leaf's AIA "CA Issuers" URI or have
#   it cached), but Node's global `fetch` (undici) does NOT, and rejects the
#   handshake with UNABLE_TO_VERIFY_LEAF_SIGNATURE. Bundling the intermediate here
#   and adding it to the trust `ca` list for cac.es lets TLS verification stay FULLY
#   ON (rejectUnauthorized:true) — we complete the chain ourselves instead of
#   disabling the check. The leaf is still validated up to a real public root
#   (DigiCert Global Root G2, already in Node's bundled roots).
#
# CHAIN:  *.cac.es  ->  PerfectSSL (this cert)  ->  DigiCert Global Root G2 (Node root)
#
# THIS CERT (the intermediate):
#   subject:  /C=NL/O=PerfectSSL/CN=PerfectSSL
#   issuer:   /C=US/O=DigiCert Inc/OU=www.digicert.com/CN=DigiCert Global Root G2
#   notBefore: Apr 17 00:00:00 2024 GMT
#   notAfter:  Apr 16 23:59:59 2034 GMT   <-- EXPIRY: rotate this file before then,
#                                             or when a cac.es ingest starts failing
#                                             again with UNABLE_TO_VERIFY_LEAF_SIGNATURE.
#   SHA256 fingerprint:
#     6B:40:D3:DB:AA:D6:8B:E6:E8:04:E3:20:85:F7:83:7C:EE:08:B7:C4:FA:6A:99:0B:36:22:7A:6D:CF:F0:87:3B
#
# SOURCE (the leaf's AIA CA-Issuers URI):
#   http://cacerts.digicert.com/PerfectSSL.crt   (downloaded as DER, converted to PEM)
#
# TO REFRESH (when it rotates):
#   1. openssl x509 -in <(echo | openssl s_client -connect cac.es:443 -servername cac.es 2>/dev/null) \
#        -noout -text | grep -A6 "Authority Information Access"   # find the new CA-Issuers URI
#   2. curl -s -o new.crt <that-URI>
#   3. openssl x509 -inform DER -in new.crt -outform PEM -out new.pem
#   4. confirm:  openssl x509 -in new.pem -noout -subject  ==  the leaf's issuer
#   5. replace the PEM block below + update the subject/issuer/dates/fingerprint above.
